CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, October 20, 1945, pg. 1, reads: "[illegible] Co-Ed - Miss Marilyn Ware, daughter of Mr. and Mrs. Seymour Ware of Paulson Avenue, winner of this year's Robert L. Vann scholarship, is pictured catching up with her studies on the University of Pitt campus.  Miss Ware is a graduate of Westinghouse High School. -  Courier Photo by Harris."
TitMainTitle: Marilyn Ware (Parker) seated on lawn of the Cathedral of Learning, University of Pittsburgh, with Heinz Chapel, Mellon Institute, and Young Men and Women's Hebrew Association in background, Oakland
